This is delicious recipe. It is sweet, but not overpowering, and both simple and fast to make. I soaked the raisins overnight in the brandy, and used pecans instead of walnuts, because that is what we had on hand. Beware of boiling the sweet potatoes too long; while the dish still has a wonderful flavor, it gets a little mushy.

